The paper discusses an unsupervised learning approach for detecting abnormalities in resting-state dynamics using autoencoder and next frame prediction strategies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which could place it in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the study of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), which are other possible sub-categories.
